[{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"CurrentModule = QuasiPeriodicHelmholtz","category":"page"},{"location":"#QuasiPeriodicHelmholtz","page":"Home","title":"QuasiPeriodicHelmholtz","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Documentation for QuasiPeriodicHelmholtz.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Modules = [QuasiPeriodicHelmholtz]","category":"page"},{"location":"#QuasiPeriodicHelmholtz.NaiveGreensFunction2D","page":"Home","title":"QuasiPeriodicHelmholtz.NaiveGreensFunction2D","text":"G = NaiveGreensFunction2D(wavenumber,period,theta)\n\nG(x,ξ;M)\n\nComputes 2D quasi-periodic Greens function for Helmholtz equation with\n\nk = wavenumber(G)\n\nthat is quasi-periodic with f([x,y],[ξ,η]) = exp(imkdcos(θ))f([ξ+d,η]) where\n\nd = period(G)\nθ = theta(G)\n\nby summation of the free space Greens Function for 2M+1 closest periods\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#QuasiPeriodicHelmholtz.TailGreensFunction2D","page":"Home","title":"QuasiPeriodicHelmholtz.TailGreensFunction2D","text":"G = TailGreensFunction2D(wavenumber,period,theta)\n\nG(x,ξ;M)\n\nComputes 2D quasi-periodic Greens function for Helmholtz equation with\n\nk = wavenumber(G)\n\nthat is quasi-periodic with f(x,y) = exp(imxcos(θ))*f(x+d,y) where\n\nd = period(G)\nθ = angle(G)\n\nby summation of the free space Greens Function for 2M-1 closest periods, and approximating the tail asymptotically to order M^{-5/2}\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"}]
